race.comment: The maiden stayers kick us off. BRAIN WAVE (5) only went down by a narrow margin at Grafton last time out and looks to be knocking on the door of a maiden victory. Lerena was in the irons for that last-start placing and sticks here. Rates the testing material. The well-related WEEKEND ARTIST (4) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed I'm All The Talk) has placed four of eight around this circuit and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Looms as the only danger. KIRORO PEAK (1) will be rock-hard fit for this and may be able to run into the placings. CHAYSE'N' THE KING (6) has had a few chances but can earn some minor money with the right run. SAVEA (2) next in line by default.
